274
00:12:56,870 --> 00:12:59,225
sometimes called the replay

275
00:12:59,225 --> 00:13:02,705
buffer in reinforcement
learning algorithm.

276
00:13:02,705 --> 00:13:04,880
For now, we're just flying

277
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:07,640
the lunar lander randomly,
sometimes crashing,

278
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:09,590
sometimes not and getting

279
00:13:09,590 --> 00:13:13,205
these tuples as experienced
for our learning algorithm.

280
00:13:13,205 --> 00:13:17,060
Occasionally then we will
train the neural network.

281
00:13:17,060 --> 00:13:18,650
In order to train

282
00:13:18,650 --> 00:13:21,185
the neural network,
here's what we'll do.

283
00:13:21,185 --> 00:13:23,210
We'll look at these 10,000 most

284
00:13:23,210 --> 00:13:25,700
recent tuples we had saved and

285
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:30,560
create a training set
of 10,000 examples.

286
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:34,340
Training set needs lots
of pairs of x and y.

287
00:13:34,340 --> 00:13:36,980
For our training examples,

288
00:13:36,980 --> 00:13:39,230
x will be the s,

289
00:13:39,230 --> 00:13:41,975
a from this part of the tuple.

290
00:13:41,975 --> 00:13:43,805
There'll be a list
of 12 numbers,

291
00:13:43,805 --> 00:13:45,470
the 8 numbers for the state and

292
00:13:45,470 --> 00:13:48,470
the 4 numbers for the one-hot
encoding of the action.

293
00:13:48,470 --> 00:13:50,750
The target value that we want

294
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:53,090
a neural network
to try to predict

295
00:13:53,090 --> 00:13:57,800
would be y equals R of S
plus Gamma max of a prime,

296
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:59,825
Q of s prime a prime.

297
00:13:59,825 --> 00:14:01,910
How do we get this value of Q?

298
00:14:01,910 --> 00:14:03,380
Well, initially is

299
00:14:03,380 --> 00:14:06,245
this neural network that we
had randomly initialized.

300
00:14:06,245 --> 00:14:07,640
It may not be a very good guess,

301
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,065
but it's a guess.

302
00:14:09,065 --> 00:14:11,300
After creating these 10,000

303
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:15,050
training examples we'll
have training examples x1,

304
00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:22,160
y1 through x10,000, y10,000.

305
00:14:22,160 --> 00:14:24,200
We'll train a neural network

306
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:27,365
and I'm going to call the
new neural network Q new,

307
00:14:27,365 --> 00:14:30,050
such that Q new of s,

308
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:33,335
a learns to approximate y.

309
00:14:33,335 --> 00:14:35,810
This is exactly training that

310
00:14:35,810 --> 00:14:40,025
neural network to output f
with parameters w and b,

311
00:14:40,025 --> 00:14:45,350
to input x to try to
approximate the target value y.

312
00:14:45,350 --> 00:14:48,320
Now, this neural
network should be

313
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:50,825
a slightly better
estimates of what

314
00:14:50,825 --> 00:14:51,980
the Q function or

315
00:14:51,980 --> 00:14:54,185
the state action value
function should be.

316
00:14:54,185 --> 00:14:57,950
What we'll do is we're going
to take Q and set it to

317
00:14:57,950 --> 00:15:01,925
this new neural network
that we had just learned.

318
00:15:01,925 --> 00:15:06,530
Many of the ideas in this
algorithm are due to Mnih et al.

319
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:10,114
It turns out that if
you run this algorithm

320
00:15:10,114 --> 00:15:11,750
where you start with

321
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:14,435
a really random guess
of the Q function,

322
00:15:14,435 --> 00:15:16,520
then use Bellman's equations to

323
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:18,380
repeatedly try to improve

324
00:15:18,380 --> 00:15:20,180
the estimates of the Q function.

325
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:22,370
Then by doing this
over and over,

326
00:15:22,370 --> 00:15:23,585
taking lots of actions,

327
00:15:23,585 --> 00:15:25,355
training a model, that will

328
00:15:25,355 --> 00:15:28,145
